result.execSummary:
The defendant Kari A Moss was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Methamphetamine, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(g).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

(2:30 PM cases 22CF82, 22CF434 called.) Prosecuting attorney Matthew Z Kirkpatrick in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Kari A Moss in court, in custody. Attorney Roger M Hillestad in court for Kari A Moss.
Parties advise are stipulating to the findings of the report and move the defendant be found competent.
Parties request the report be sealed.
Court finds the defendant is competent to proceed.
Court orders the report is to be sealed.
Defendant waives right to a preliminary hearing in 22CF82 and Court accepts waiver. 
State advises will file an Information in 22CF82 which will mirror the complaint. Attorney Hillestad advises can proceed forward without the Information on file.
Defendant pleads No Contest to 22CF82 Count 1: Possession of Methamphetamine.
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
Court accepts the defendant's Guilty plea and finds the defendant Guilty of 22CF82 Count 1.

Court withholds sentence and places the defendant on probation for 2 years with the following conditions:
AODA and follow through with recommendations. Complete a Mental Health Assessment and follow through with recommendations. Maintain absolute sobriety. No contact with any known drug dealers/users, except in a therapeutic setting. Not to go into any taverns, bars, liquor stores/place where alcohol is primarily served/sold. Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge and pay court costs. 108 days credit if probation revoked. Any remaining charges including cases 22CF434, 22TR569 are dismissed and read in.
